            <h2 class="custom-header"><strong>Miracle of the Kandyan Forest Gardens</strong></h2>
        </div>
        <div class="custom-details">
            <p>
                With the coffee devastation, Sri Lankan Arabica Coffee was confined entirely to the
                Kandyan Forest Gardens(KFG). KFG, an analog forest to tropical rain forest, was originally
                man made, but nature has taken over with passing generations. This Agro Forestry system
                is essentially organic since no agro chemicals are used and no maintenance is done at all.
            </p>
            <p>
                The coffee grown under this system has an intrinsic quality because of the geography and
                unusual micro climatic conditions in this region. Therefore, this coffee growing at around
                1000m elevation above sea level with a tropical climate, carries unique flavours and aromas
                superior to any other in the world.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
