            <p>
                In 2006 Japan Fair Trade Committee (JFTC), a leading coffee business group in Japan, visited
                Sri Lanka and identified the potential of rejuvenating the Sri Lankan Arabica coffee industry
                that had all but vanished. Then in 2007, with the collaborative support of Japan Internation Cooperation
                Agency(JICA), JFTC and Department of Export Agriculture Sri Lanka (DEA), a coffee development project
                was launched based in the central hill country.
            </p>
            <p>
                JFTC opened the pathway to sell the quality coffee produced by the project to the eager Japanese market with a
                vision of "fair price for coffee, good life for farmers and consumers happy with rare, superior quality coffee".
                Because of this, Japanese coffee connoisseurs and amateurs alike have been enjoying the extraordinary coffee
                taste that was almost lost to the world, since 2008.
            </p>
            <p>
                Ceilao Gosto Coffee Shop is the marketing arm of the JAPAN SRI LANKA FRIENDSHIP ASSOICATION Coffee Project,
                which is supported by the Department of Agricultural Export of the Sri Lankan Government, JAICA.
                The objective of this project is to revitalize the halcyon days of Sri Lankan coffee.
                The project is supported by the Department of Export Agricultural of the Sri Lankan Government,
                which is responsible for the coffee development programme from its grassroots to the consumers through the stakeholder channel.
            </p>
